CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1779311467
OL,3,CNigel Farage: Makerfield by-election
OL,4,Cis 'biggest in half a century'
OL,6,FIf he returns to Parliament, the three-
OL,7,Ftime Mayor and former Leigh MP is
OL,8,Fwidely expected to challenge Sir Keir
OL,9,FStarmer for the Labour leadership, but
OL,10,Fthe Prime Minister has insisted he
OL,11,Fwill not "walk away" from Downing
OL,12,FStreet.
OL,14,FAnnouncing his party's candidate, Mr
OL,15,FFarage described the contest as a
OL,16,F"David versus Goliath battle".
OL,18,FMr Kenyon ran in the Makerfield
OL,19,Fconstituency in the General Election
OL,20,Fin 2024, coming second to Labour's
OL,21,FJosh Simmons.
OL,26,@sD@JOUsD@TO]xD@AOUxD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
