CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1779311467
OL,3,CNigel Farage: Makerfield by-election
OL,4,Cis 'biggest in half a century'
OL,6,FMr Farage told ITV News Reform UK
OL,7,F"will throw the kitchen sink" at the
OL,8,Fby-election, stating: "We're going to
OL,9,Fback our plucky plumber to take on the
OL,10,Fso-called king of the North and may
OL,11,Fthe best man win."
OL,13,FHe said the party's priority in the
OL,14,Fregion would be to ease pressure on
OL,15,Fsocial housing.
OL,17,FHe said: "In this constituency,
OL,18,Fgoodness knows, no one knows. 200, 300
OL,19,FHMOs in this constituency, and many of
OL,20,Fthose people will be those who came
OL,21,Finto Britain illegally."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
